The paper presents a deep learning model for restoring missing characters in ancient Greek inscriptions. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as language modeling and sequence prediction, which are commonly studied in the computer science subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The model also uses deep neural networks, which are a core component of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper's focus on deep learning and neural networks also suggests that it could fall under the subfield of deep learning (cs.DL). Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval (IR) techniques, as it deals with searching for and restoring missing information in a corpus of texts. Finally, the paper's use of machine learning to improve upon human performance in a specific task could also fall under the subfield of machine learning (cs.LG).
